        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 12:17PM MDT by NWS Riverton WY</headline>
        <description>At 1216 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 11 miles south of Salt River Pass to Sage
Junction. Movement was northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Cokeville and Sage Junction around 1220 PM MDT.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
